<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - REMOVE - REVERSE
        IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1302005" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="7">
        <title>REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Before the upper reverse idler gear assembly can be removed, the mainshaft reverse gear must be positioned
            forward against the next gear.
        </para>
        <para>While removing the reverse idler shaft, the thrust washer can drop to the transmission case bottom.</para>
        <para>The mainshaft reverse gear must be moved to remove the upper reverse idler gear. Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s13020_HL1302006.xml" xrefid="hl1302006">4.14.</hotlnk>, Mainshaft Assembly, steps 1-3.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the lock nut and washer from the idler shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302037">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302037" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302037" filename="../figg13/G1302037.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Idler Shaft Lock Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The mainshaft reverse gear must be moved to remove the upper reverse idler gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302038">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302038" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302038" filename="../figg13/G1302038.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Upper Reverse Idler Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the loosened lock nut and washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302038">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the pipe plug from the idler shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302039">Figure 39</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302039" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302039" filename="../figg13/G1302039.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Pipe Plug</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use an impact puller to remove the auxiliary countershaft front bearing race from the
                reverse idler gear bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302040">Figure 40</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302040" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302040" filename="../figg13/G1302040.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 40. Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install an impact puller, 1/2"-13 threaded end, and remove the shaft from case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302041">Figure 41</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302041" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302041" filename="../figg13/G1302041.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. Shaft From Case Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">As the idler shaft and idler plate are removed, remove the thrust washers and gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302042">Figure 42</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302042" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302042" filename="../figg13/G1302042.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Thrust Washers &#38; Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the reverse gear assembly; replace the inner race and needle bearing if necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302043">Figure 43</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302043" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302043" filename="../figg13/G1302043.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. Reverse Gear Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
